  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM10.6.2">
<l>kuṉṟoṉ ṟumattā varava maḷavik kuraimā kaṭalaik kaṭaintiṭ ṭorukāl</l>
<l>niṉṟuṇ ṭaikoṇṭōṭ ṭivaṅkūṉ nimira niṉainta perumā ṉatuvaṉ ṟiyummuṉ</l>
<l>naṉṟuṇ ṭatolcīr makarak kaṭalēḻ malaiyē ḻulakē ḻoḻiyā mainampi</l>
<l>yaṉṟuṇ ṭavaṉkāṇ miṉiṉṟāyc ciyarā laḷaiveṇ ṇeyuṇṭāp puṇṭirun tavaṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The great lord who, having churned up the great roaring sea</l>
<l rend="indent">with a mountain as the rod, turning it with a serpent [as the rope],</l>
<l>One time decided to permanently straighten a cruel humpback [woman],</l>
<l rend="indent">taking and shooting balls [of clay],</l>
<l>The one who, besides that, once consumed, craving without ceasing,</l>
<l rend="indent">the goodness-imbued, ancient, fine, makara[-filled] seven seas,</l>
<l>Seven mountains, and seven worlds, see, he is the one who was bound,</l>
<l rend="indent">having eaten the butter churned by the herder women today.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
